JOHANNESBURG - Axed former State Security Agency (SSA) top spy and Jacob Zuma ally, Thulani Dlomo, has denied any involvement in the organising of unrest over the past week. He is accused of being one of 12 people fuelling rioting and looting in KwaZulu-Natal and Gauteng. READ: Violence in SA | Our military is capable - govt Police are yet to confirm reports that he has handed himself over to authorities. The former ambassador to Japan spoke via telephone to eNCA's Siphamandla Goge in the video above.